# CHALLENGES_AND_LEARNINGS.pdf
## Introduction

During the implementation of this project, several challenges were encountered while working with Terraform, Jenkins, Docker, ECS, and AWS services.

Resolving these issues provided valuable troubleshooting experience and improved understanding of DevOps practices.

---
## Challenge 1 - Jenkins Executor Offline
### Error
Waiting for next available executor.
### Root Cause
The Jenkins node became unavailable because available disk space was below the configured threshold.

### Resolution
* Cleaned temporary files.
* Released disk space.
* Brought the Jenkins node back online.

### Learning
Always monitor Jenkins node health and storage usage.

---

## Challenge 2 - terraform.tfvars File Missing
### Error
Failed to read variables file.
terraform.tfvars does not exist.
### Root Cause
The Terraform pipeline was executed from an incorrect directory.

### Resolution
Verified the workspace structure using:
* pwd
* ls -la
* find .
Updated the pipeline path.

### Learning
Always verify the current working directory before running Terraform commands.

---

## Challenge 3 - No Configuration Files
### Error
No configuration files found.
### Root Cause
The folder name in Jenkins did not match the actual repository structure.
Terraform expected:
Terraform
Actual folder:
Terrafrom

### Resolution
Corrected the folder path inside the Jenkins pipeline.
### Learning
Naming consistency is critical in automation.

---

## Challenge 4 - CloudWatch Module Error
### Error
Unreadable module directory.
### Root Cause
Terraform expected:
CloudWatch
Actual folder name:
Cloudwatch

### Resolution
Updated the module source path.

### Learning
Terraform module paths are case-sensitive.

---
## Challenge 5 - AWS Credentials Error
### Error
No valid credential sources found.
### Root Cause
Terraform backend could not access AWS credentials.

### Resolution
Configured AWS credentials within Jenkins.

### Learning
Terraform backend authentication must be configured before initialization.

---

## Challenge 6 - RDS Subnet Group Error
### Error
Invalid subnet group name.
### Root Cause
Resource naming configuration was invalid.

### Resolution
Corrected subnet group naming values.

### Learning
AWS naming conventions must always be followed.

---

## Challenge 7 - Docker Login Failure
### Error
400 Bad Request during ECR login.

### Root Cause
The ECR repository URL was used instead of the ECR registry URL.

### Resolution
Updated the Docker login command with the correct ECR registry endpoint.

### Learning
Understand the difference between ECR Registry and ECR Repository.

---

## Challenge 8 - ECS Image Pull Failure
### Error
CannotPullContainerError
Image latest not found.
### Root Cause
The application image was pushed using build numbers instead of the latest tag.

### Resolution
Updated the Jenkins pipeline to push:
8byte-app:latest

### Learning
A consistent image tagging strategy is important for deployments.

---

## Challenge 9 - Application Not Accessible
### Root Cause Investigation
Verified:
* ECS Service
* ECS Tasks
* Security Groups
* Target Group
* Application Load Balancer
* CloudWatch Logs

### Resolution
Validated networking, target group configuration, and container port mapping.

### Learning
Application troubleshooting should follow a structured approach from Load Balancer to Container.
http://8byte-alb-2116250128.ap-south-1.elb.amazonaws.com
---

